(600, 'Notes: Surfacing Polytrade which is currently raising $5-6 M seed round. Team comes highly referenced from key crypto angels, have just launched their protocol and are now nearing the first $1M financing activity mark. There is high momentum to this round with Falcon, Sequoia India, Coinbase ventures, Draper Dragon, Hashed, Saison, already in advanced stages + early stage web3 funds already putting out TSs. We are excited because 1. A key thesis area in crypto for us is Defi-TradFi bridging 1. A complete team which has already shipped the protocol and cold started liquidity + financing cycle 1. Founder has great depth and experience in the underlying finance business (invoice discounting). We’d be looking out for - Execution risks : eg: currently routing fiat via DBS bank at SGP which could be a risk if DBS decides to not accept crypto as source of funds? what can be done to mitigate?) - Regulatory risks : KYC requirements, AML concerns etc - Accrual of value to equity and tokens cap tables and tokenomics + role of community in growth (investor GTM, future protocol growth) - Growth mindset and coachability of founder We are completing BRCs, expert conversations and lining up a founder convo with fin-tech team (Anish, AK) this week before bringing this to a meeting with you early next week. **About** [Polytrade](https://polytrade.finance/) is a trade finance co bridging DeFi (decentralised finance) and TradFI (traditional finance) using smart contracts and tokenomics. They bri...'),
(602, 'Z47 notes from @Pranay Desai: Given Murf and potential conflict, no chance we invest in one more. My view – WMB and pass - Entrepreneurial - Hacker type profile - potential technical spike (but have to validate) ? Business hole clear ? Exposure missing – first-time founder mistakes **Met **[**Sudarshan**](https://ind01.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fin%2Fsudarshankamath%2F&data=05%7C02%7Cashwin%40z47.com%7C6dd85b6ba95743e7507708dd08ff00d6%7C64b15078ddc041d8aab3f9170e15cc08%7C0%7C0%7C638676613502472395%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&sdata=UDFUPGyoAX24tfrFZUHGa3K8VJHe0EXgp6tXV1I6RVs%3D&reserved=0)** @ Smallest AI** WMB and pass. Tinkerers who want to cool tech but not focussed on business building. We should track this via 3one4 to see if they are inflecting on business side. + Hacker and tinkering since he''s been in school + Strong AI ML talent + In touch with the latest papers and research in their domain + Product is good - decent audio output with 100ms latency + Learning and thoughtful - has spoken to 100ms, murf, etc and has some thoughtful learnings from these conversations - one of the reasons I am not putting this in pass forever category. +/? All over the place on ICP and market - end vision is to be application but also want to give out the voice API ? Thesis is to build conversational tooling for app layer but they don’t have a v...'),
(3900, 'RM notes: - EzoCare acquired for Tech by Apollo - Induced AI - moved out in Sept ‘25 - Doing workflow transformation for boring businesses - AI native services type company - Acqui-hire happening here - Started as agentic browser - Over 1M runs - this was BPO heavy - so focused on BPO - $1.1M on $14M post money incl. YC note - $4M - cap TBD - 4 stages of AI - Co-pilots & tools - Agents - Bespoke agents - A2A communication - Pipeline - Heads of AI COEs - CIOs who are provisioned to deploy AI - 20 Enterprises - 1K to 150K count - Genpact - spoke to leadership for NVIDIA meeting - 600 employee POC at Washington - “Don’t position as a DSP replacement tool” - 2 informal pilots - Team - 2 engineers - 1 designer in India ### Action Items ### Company Overview ### Founder Background ### Product and Market Positioning - **Initial positioning**: Targeted CISOs with AI usage visibility and security tools - **Current positioning**: Pivoted to CIOs and heads of AI Centers of Excellence who are responsible for AI deployment and adoption - **Value proposition**: Provides visibility into AI tool usage across organization, helps create both security and adoption policies, and moves from written policies to enforcement ### Traction and Pipeline - **Current pipeline**: Over 20 enterprises, ranging from 1,000 to 150,000 employees - **Design partnerships**: Two informal design partners testing on personal devices and small teams to provide feedback before formal procurement - **Genpak POC**: 150,0...')
